Hello CD, we’ve been experiencing a strange error with Phoenix6 and was wondering if someone could provide some guidance. We are able to successfully deploy code to the RoboRIO, however console printouts indicate that the library is throwing a FileNotFound error when our code attempts to construct a CANCoder object. The code does not error out in the simulator and worked within the past couple of days on last year’s swerve drivetrain for absolute encoders.

Specs and relevant stack trace are given below:

Specs

RIO type: RoboRIO 1
Language: Python
RobotPy version: 2025.2.1.0
WPILib version: 2025.2.1
Phoenix6 version: 25.1.0
CANCoder firmware: CANCoder-vH-25.1.0.0-Phoenix6.crf

Offending code (line 80 in swerve_module.py)

self.absolute_encoder = phoenix6.hardware.CANcoder(self.id_lookup["absolute_encoder"])

self.id_lookup["absolute_encoder"] is an integer of the CAN ID of the encoder.

Stack trace

The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.
